message.entry: Not enough input arguments. See ODE15s.
The mass matrix must have some non-zero entries.
y0 and yp0 have different lengths.
Option ''NonNegativeVariables'' ignored. For linearly implicit systems, the solver does not constrain the solution.
Failure at t={0}. Unable to meet integration tolerances without reducing the step size below the smallest value allowed ({1}) at time t.
{0} must be a function handle that returns a sparse or full matrix.
Dynamic memory allocation must be enabled to generate code for {0}.
